<dl id="n10051g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10051g">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10051g"> 51(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> gummy</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Notre g&eacute;n&eacute;ration, fortun&eacute;e, contemporaine des enveloppes <mark>gomm&eacute;es</mark>, ne se figure pas ce qu&apos;&eacute;tait une lettre il y a cinquante ans &agrave; peine, au temps o&ugrave; le pain &agrave; cacheter figurait &agrave; la bonne place sur les bureaux. <font color="green">[Our fortunate generation is contemporaneous with gummed envelopes and never would imagine what a letter was like just fifty years ago, when a bar of sealing wax took pride of place on every desk.]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 109-10</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01023h" href="c01all.htm#c01023h">VI.C.01:023(h)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
